Leetcode problem no. 271. Encode and Decode Strings - Explanation

Description
Design an algorithm to encode a list of strings to a string. The encoded string is then sent over the network and is decoded back to the original list of strings.

Solution:

LeetCode 271: Encode and Decode Strings converts List<String> to single string (encode) and back (decode). No serialization libraries; must handle empty strings, delimiters in content.
​
#Java Implementation (Length Prefix)

public class Codec {
    private static final String DELIM = "#";
    
    // Encodes a list of strings to a single string.
    public String encode(List<String> strs) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (String s : strs) {
            sb.append(s.length()).append(DELIM).append(s);
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
    
    // Decodes a single string to a list of strings.
    public List<String> decode(String s) {
        List<String> result = new ArrayList<>();
        int i = 0;
        while (i < s.length()) {
            // Parse length
            int len = 0;
            while (i < s.length() && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))) {
                len = len * 10 + (s.charAt(i++) - '0');
            }
            // Skip delimiter
            if (i < s.length() && s.charAt(i) == '#') i++;
            // Extract string
            String str = s.substring(i, i + len);
            result.add(str);
            i += len;
        }
        return result;
    }
}

Length prefix: len#string format. "Hello" → "5#Hello"; "World" → "5#World".
​
#Step-by-Step Logic
Encode:
For each string: append length + "#" + string
Return concatenated result
Decode:
Index i = 0
While i < length:
Read digits → len
Skip '#'
Extract s.substring(i, i+len)
i += len

#Thought Process
Problem: Strings can contain ANY chars (spaces, digits, '#'). Simple delimiter fails.
Solution: Prefix length tells exactly where string ends. 5#Hello3#Hi → unambiguous.
Why '#': Non-digit separator. Length digits unambiguous from string content.
Time: O(total chars), Space: O(total chars).
​
#Edge Cases
Empty strings: [""] → "0#" → decodes correctly.
Empty list: [] → "" → empty list.
Numbers in strings: "123" → "35#123" (3 chars, not value).
Long strings: Length up to 10^5 total chars.
Delimiter in content: "a#b" → "3#a#b" → perfect.
Single string: ["abc"] → "3#abc".
